{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781761951241,"sessionID":"ses_126b79683ffe1J61Cb0HgstWBi","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_6wahAkHRvwlaVu2gPRpmFXrJ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"A-search-retrieval|search retrieval|retrieval|candidate|graphless|code_graph|Grep|memory_search|memory_context","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation","include":"*.md"},"output":"Found 100 matches (more matches available)\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/scopes/A-search-retrieval/spec.md:\n  Line 4: Independent gpt-5.5 deep-review **audit** of the search/retrieval code of the system-spec-kit MCP server. This is a REVIEW-SCOPE target — there is NO new implementation to verify. Audit the shipped code below for real defects and report P0/P1/P2 findings with `file:line` evidence. Do not invent findings; a clean PASS is a valid outcome.\n\n  Line 8: - `lib/search/pipeline/stage1-*.ts`, `lib/search/pipeline/stage2-fusion.ts` — candidate generation + post-fusion scoring signals\n\n  Line 11: - BM25 field weights, hybrid search scope-then-limit, vector read-path resilience, retrieval gating & recall recovery (search/retrieval modules under `lib/search/` and `lib/`)\n\n  Line 18: Round-1 already audited the 017-021 fixes (cancel-delay, calibration PAV pooling, cache mtime invalidation, confidence 3-factor weights). This round BROADENS to the whole search/retrieval surface — focus on code those fixes did not directly touch.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/scopes/B-rest-of-002/spec.md:\n  Line 4: Independent gpt-5.5 deep-review **audit** of the memory store, index, and write-lifecycle code of the system-spec-kit MCP server — the 002-memory-store-and-search surface OUTSIDE the search/retrieval pipeline and outside the 017-021 fixes. REVIEW-SCOPE target (no new implementation). Report real P0/P1/P2 findings with `file:line` evidence; clean PASS is valid.\n\n  Line 11: - semantic trigger fallback, learning-feedback reducers, memclaw-derived memory hardening, OpenLTM retrieval/observability + continuity/resilience, provenance injection, idempotency flag-on correctness (the 002 store/index modules under `handlers/` and `lib/`)\n\n  Line 17: This round BROADENS beyond 017-021. Focus on store/index/lifecycle code, not the search/retrieval pipeline (covered by scope A).\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/decision-record.md:\n  Line 140: Several findings were filed at P1 by individual lineages and then DOWNGRADED to P2 by the synthesizer after re-verifying against code: the 019/020 marker schema/TTL drift (predicate reads only `childPid`/`activeUntilMs`, zero runtime impact), the 021 A1 empty-files `timedPhase` gap (every phase on the branch is bounded or yields), and the 017 doc scaffold cluster. Conversely, several P1/P0-candidate findings were verified FALSE-POSITIVE: 018 mimo-1 post-restart fast-cancel (crash recovery resets jobs to `failed`), and the 020 D6/D7/D8 atomic-write-throw family (`atomicWriteFile` never throws — it returns `false`).\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/lineages/gpt55r2-a-smoke/resource-map.md:\n  Line 12: | `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/pipeline/stage1-candidate-gen.ts` | F002 |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/lineages/gpt55r2-a-smoke/deep-review-strategy.md:\n  Line 4: Search and retrieval audit for the system-spec-kit MCP server.\n\n  Line 29: - Directly compared summary-embedding retrieval against vector and FTS retrieval scope predicates.\n\n  Line 42: If this lineage continues, review security and cancellation surfaces in the remaining handlers and retrieval fallback paths, then replay F001/F002 after remediation.\n\n  Line 45: - Scope file: `.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/scopes/A-search-retrieval/spec.md`.\n\n  Line 46: - The scope states there is no new implementation to verify and asks for real defects in `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/` search/retrieval code.\n\n  Line 52: | core | spec_code | partial | Scope requests search/retrieval audit; F001/F002 map to recall, scope, and recovery risks. |\n\n  Line 54: | overlay | feature_catalog_code | partial | Search/retrieval feature catalog comments were present in reviewed code. |\n\n  Line 61: | `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/pipeline/stage1-candidate-gen.ts` | reviewed | F002 source; summary hydration/filtering. |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/lineages/gpt55r2-a-1/resource-map.md:\n  Line 4: - Novel logic gaps: F001 in sqlite lexical fusion and F002 in summary embedding scoped retrieval.\n\n  Line 11: | `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/hybrid-search.ts` | Hybrid retrieval orchestration and lexical fusion | F001 |\n\n  Line 13: | `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/memory-summaries.ts` | Summary embedding retrieval | F002 |\n\n  Line 14: | `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/pipeline/stage1-candidate-gen.ts` | Stage 1 candidate collection and post-filtering | F002 |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/lineages/gpt55r2-a-smoke/iterations/iteration-001.md:\n  Line 8: - `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/pipeline/stage1-candidate-gen.ts`\n\n  Line 29: - **F002**: Summary lane uses weaker active/scope filtering than the primary retrieval lanes. Stage 1 hydrates summary hits with `SELECT ... FROM memory_index WHERE id IN (...)` and no `active_memory_projection` join, then applies `applyFolderFilter()`, which requires exact `rowSpecFolder === specFolder`. Vector and FTS paths apply subtree scope predicates before returning rows, and vector joins `active_memory_projection`. This means the summary lane can score/hydrate IDs under different active-row semantics and can drop descendant spec-folder hits that primary lanes retain. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/pipeline/stage1-candidate-gen.ts:1322-1343] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/pipeline/stage1-candidate-gen.ts:139-147] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/vector-index-queries.ts:84-92] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/vector-index-queries.ts:432-455] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/sqlite-fts.ts:183-205]\n\n  Line 43:   \"counterevidenceSought\": \"Checked the caller in stage1-candidate-gen.ts and the summary module for a later corpus-wide rerank, scoped prefilter, ORDER BY, active projection join, or vect